  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 512a72de08c75cf4e8a8424f7b75a271, type: 3}
  m_Name: D4T6_AdvisorSqueezeIndian_Dialogue
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  npc: 0
  sequence:
  - dialogueText: So, the search continues? The Boss seems remarkably focused on
      that thief.
    buttonText: He's losing it
  - dialogueText: 'Let him be. My advice remains the same as last time: play it cool.
      Don''t let his paranoia become your problem.'
    buttonText: Just wait?
  - dialogueText: Correct. A larger event will eventually occur, and this theft will
      become a footnote. It's just a matter of time
    buttonText: Something bigger?
  - dialogueText: Things can't stay this quiet forever. In the meantime, look at
      the Indian. He's the architect of your current situation.
    buttonText: What do you mean?
  - dialogueText: He placed you here. Personally, I think you shouldn't be handling
      his jobs for mere pocket change.
    buttonText: Squeeze him?
  - dialogueText: It would be the logical move. He has information that is far more
      valuable than your salary
    buttonText: I'll do it
  - dialogueText: Okay. That way you won't be the only one paying a debt you didn't
      sign for.
    buttonText: Right
